channel.title: Ok, i need help running ANY of my servers
channel.description:
aight, i have about 3 servers, like pimpscape for example. I have questions.
1. First question, While i am compiling, should i have moparscape window on, and when i run should i have moparscape window on?
2. Another question, whenever i run after i compile, the run message comes up in a blink of a second, then goes away, so i keep clicking and it keeps appearing then disapearing, is this normal?
3. Last question, after i succesfully compile and run (if you guys tell me how to do it right) what do i enter in the moparscape window, i already set up my no-ip account and have a ip thingy, do i enter the numbers or the actual name, or something else.[br][size=1]Posted on: November 16, 2007, 09:46:02 PM[/size][hr]no one?[br][size=1]Posted on: November 16, 2007, 10:04:21 PM[/size][hr]um, hello, help?[br][size=1]Posted on: November 16, 2007, 10:31:06 PM[/size][hr]helllllooooo? this is a big deal to me, i cant play anything i made

item.description:
@Goddess wrote:

gosh dang ok first i will say do this again and i promise ppl will be alot meaner than i am. it makes you look stupid it really does.

  1. The client has nothing to do with the server you are running. Completely separate and everything. So no it doesnt.
  2. Lol ok you dont have to compile every time before you run. Compiling just saves the edits and allows the new system to be run. The disappearing means you have a bad run server. Give me one second and ill post you mine.
  3. Ok if you have made a no-ip then just enter it. you can then get on. Generally its port 43594 for most basic sources. But if you havent port forwarded you will be the only one with access.

DONT Quad post!!

crakaman. the runserver goes away fast. it isnt the compiler. lol! read it next time.[br][size=1]Posted on: November 17, 2007, 12:16:05 AM[/size][hr]and driger stop spamming please. this is a place to help ppl :\ he knows we said it all. or we wouldnt have said it?
